[2026-07-13] Voice/Video calling — full Agora client built (frontend only)
  - Feature request: build the complete FRONT-END for voice/video calling
    using Agora, so the whole flow exists client-side and a detailed backend
    handoff can be sent. User confirmed two design choices: (a) Agora token
    minted server-side via a Supabase Edge Function (`get-agora-token`);
    (b) incoming-call ring signaled via Supabase Realtime on `call_logs`
    (not FCM-per-call). Both are the recommended options.
  - Architecture: MEDIA = Agora RTC; SIGNALING = existing `call_logs` table +
    Supabase Realtime. Ring/accept/decline/end are status transitions on the
    call row, observed live over realtime; Agora only carries audio/video once
    both sides join the channel (= the call's UUID).
  - Packages added (pubspec.yaml): `agora_rtc_engine: ^6.5.0` (resolved 6.5.3),
    `permission_handler: ^11.3.1` (resolved 11.4.0).
  - New config: `lib/core/config/agora_config.dart` — `AGORA_APP_ID` via
    `--dart-define` (public; App Certificate stays server-only), the
    `get-agora-token` function name, and `isConfigured`. Added an empty
    `AGORA_APP_ID` define to `.vscode/launch.json` (real id supplied at build).
  - Model: `shared/models/call_log.dart` EXTENDED — added `channelName`,
    `callerAgoraUid`, `receiverAgoraUid` (all nullable/defensive so it still
    reads today's schema), plus `otherUserId()`/`amICaller()` helpers and a
    docstring for the full status state machine.
  - Repository: `shared/data/call_repository.dart` REWRITTEN — added
    `AgoraToken`/`AgoraTokenException`; `startCall` now writes
    `call_status='ringing'`; added `answerCall`/`declineCall`/`cancelCall`/
    `markMissed`/`getAgoraToken` (Edge Function invoke)/`getCall`/
    `subscribeToIncomingCalls` (realtime INSERT filtered to receiver_id) /
    `subscribeToCall` (realtime UPDATE filtered to the call id). Kept the
    existing `endCall` (ended_at+ended_by+duration together per the DB
    constraint) and `getCallHistory`.
  - Engine wrapper: `lib/core/calls/agora_call_service.dart` (NEW) — owns one
    `RtcEngine` per call; `ensurePermissions` (mic/camera via
    permission_handler), `join`/`leave`, `toggleMic`/`toggleCamera`/
    `switchCamera`/`toggleSpeaker`, and ValueNotifiers for joined/remoteUid/
    mic/camera/speaker so the UI reacts without a full rebuild.
  - State machine: `lib/features/calls/call_state.dart` (NEW, CallPhase enum:
    idle/outgoingRinging/incomingRinging/connecting/connected/ended +
    CallEndReason) and `call_controller.dart` (NEW, StateNotifier) — drives
    the whole lifecycle: place call → insert ringing row → 35s ring timeout →
    missed; on realtime 'answered' both sides fetch a token and join Agora; on
    remote-join → connected + duration timer; hangUp writes duration/cancels;
    observes the peer's status changes and remote-leave to tear down. A
    deterministic local uid (`agoraUidFor`, stable 31-bit hash of user id) is
    used when the backend doesn't assign `*_agora_uid`. One call at a time.
  - UI: `lib/features/calls/call_screen.dart` (NEW) — single full-screen
    surface rendering every phase (outgoing/incoming/connecting/connected
    audio + video with local PiP preview, end state), brand-styled; controls
    swap per phase (accept/decline, mute/speaker/camera/flip/end). PopScope
    blocks back-abandon of a live call. `call_overlay.dart` (NEW) — mounted
    above the router via MaterialApp.router's `builder`; subscribes to incoming
    calls whenever auth settles, resolves the caller's name/photo, and pushes
    CallScreen off the controller's isActive state so a call rings on ANY
    screen.
  - Wiring: `features/chat/chat_screen.dart` — the header phone/video buttons
    now call `_startCall(video:)` (was a "coming soon" toast); resolves the
    conversation + partner and delegates to the controller.
    `features/messages/messages_screen.dart` — tapping a row in the Calls tab
    calls that person back with the same call type. Both guard on
    `AgoraConfig.isConfigured`.
  - Android manifest: added INTERNET/ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE/MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS/
    WAKE_LOCK/BLUETOOTH/BLUETOOTH_CONNECT (CAMERA + RECORD_AUDIO already
    present, reused for calls).
  - Backend handoff: `app doctumant/BACKEND_CALLS_HANDOFF.md` (NEW) — the full
    server-side contract: 3 new `call_logs` columns + channel-name trigger,
    INSERT/UPDATE RLS, the `get-agora-token` Edge Function request/response
    shape + token params + auth checks, enabling Realtime on `call_logs`, and
    an optional `notify_on_missed_call` trigger. Also documents what's out of
    scope for v1 (native ringing on killed app via FCM/CallKit, group calls,
    recording — none need TURN since Agora handles transport).
  - Result / verification: `flutter pub get` clean. `flutter analyze` → same 4
    pre-existing unrelated infos, ZERO issues in any new call file.
    `flutter build apk --debug` (with a dummy AGORA_APP_ID) → BUILT
    successfully (Agora native SDK + permission_handler compiled against a real
    Android build). `flutter test` → All tests passed (2, unchanged).
  - Open items / follow-ups: NOT run on a real device — calling needs two
    physical/emulated devices with mic/camera, a real Agora App ID, and the
    backend pieces in BACKEND_CALLS_HANDOFF.md (§1-4) live before it works
    end-to-end. This session is client-only, exactly as requested. Next:
    hand BACKEND_CALLS_HANDOFF.md to the backend team; once get-agora-token +
    the columns + realtime are live, do a two-device call test.

