[2026-07-13] Diagnosed: push notifications don't show when app is closed
  - User reported in-app notifications work but "out-of-app" (push) ones
    don't. Traced through `fcm_service.dart`: `_onForegroundMessage()`
    (line 85) only debug-prints, and `_onMessageOpenedApp()` only reads
    `message.data['type']` for tap-routing — the client was written
    assuming the backend's `send-fcm-push` payload includes a `notification`
    block (which the Android OS renders automatically, even app-closed) in
    addition to the `data` block (which only running app code can read).
    `BACKEND_PUSH_FINAL_STEPS.md` never explicitly specified this payload
